The paper discusses the performance gains that can be achieved by exploiting cross-layer information and optimizing scheduling decisions jointly over multiple flows in MPTCP. This involves considerations related to network interfaces, security, information theory, system dynamics, and performance analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.PF (Performance).
